  "body": "For nodes with validators (publishing attestations and blocks), somewhere in the first half of each epoch print to the console a summary of performance during the previous epoch, with some or all of the following info:\r\n  - Number of attestations made\r\n  - Number included on chain\r\n  - %age included on chain\r\n  - %age with correct target\r\n  - %age with correct head/block root\r\n  - min/average/max inclusion distances\r\n  - Number of blocks proposed\r\n  - Number included on chain\r\n  - Stretch goal: calculate and display the attestation effectiveness using the same algorithm as beaconcha.in (which accounts for skip slots in inclusion distance)\r\n\r\nAll of these could be useful as metrics as well. The %age of attestations included on chain, or blocks not included could be useful for alerting.",
